      {
        "type": "h2",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Performance Tuning and Scaling Strategies"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "To handle high throughput, implement connection pooling and batch requests where possible. Monitor latency using the "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "/metrics",
            "code": true
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " endpoint and adjust timeout settings based on your SLA. For distributed systems, deploy multiple API keys across regions to reduce bottlenecks. Cache frequent responses to minimize redundant calls, but ensure cache invalidation aligns with model updates."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "h2",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Error Handling and Maintenance Best Practices"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Kokoro API A returns standard HTTP status codes. Handle 4xx errors by checking request validity, and 5xx errors with retry logic using exponential backoff. Log all API interactions for auditing and debugging. Regularly rotate API keys and review access logs to prevent unauthorized use. For long-term maintenance, subscribe to Kokoro's status page for updates on deprecations or outages."
          }
        ]
